addEndpointListener

void addEndpointListener(org.osgi.service.remoteserviceadmin.EndpointListener listener,
                         String filter)
                         throws org.osgi.framework.InvalidSyntaxException
Adds the specifier EndpointListener object to the ExportRegistryImpl list of listeners. See Filter for a description of the filter syntax. EndpointListener objects are notified when an endpoint has a lifecyle state change. If the ExportRegistryImpl's list of listeners already contains listener, then this methods replaces that listner's filter with the new one.

Parameters:
listener - The EndpointListener object to be add.
filter - A valid Filter, If null all EndpointDescription are considered to match the filter.
Throws:
org.osgi.framework.InvalidSyntaxException - If the filter parameter is not a valid filter.

removeEndpointListener

void removeEndpointListener(org.osgi.service.remoteserviceadmin.EndpointListener listener)
Removes the listener object from the ExportRegistryImpl's list of EndpointListener. If listener is not contained in this ExportRegistryImpl's list of EndpointListener, this method does nothing.

Parameters:
listener - The EndpointListener to be removed.
